channel.title: Does anyone know of a working RS2 bot?
channel.description:
I was just wondering if anyone could tell me where to get a RS2 or RSC bot/autoer. I would rather have a RS2. And it would be nice if you could explain how to use it.
If this kind of question is not allowed please tell me.
Thanx

item.title: Does anyone know of a working RS2 bot?
item.dc:creator: @tL tL
item.description:
@tL wrote:

Making a java bot, like mopar said takes a lot more time, effort and skills.
Scar is a much easier way of making what you want, but i still prefer bots such as nexus pro (<3 ruler).
I have tried scar, yes it is fast but i don’t like the fact of not being able to use your computer while it is running.

As i have said many times i am not an autoer (well not for in game benefits :P).
I can run around 5 bots at a time on my computer using NeXus pro but with scar, its 1.
So you could use NeXus lite (not tried that yet) or go buy nexus pro.

Read full topic

item.title: Does anyone know of a working RS2 bot?
item.dc:creator: @The_Un-Named The Un-Named
item.description:
@The_Un-Named wrote:

shangtsung1:

Nexus is about as good as scar

No, I doubt it. A “friend” gave me Nexus 15 PRO with a tut island script, it took ALMOST 20 MINUTES to compete tutorial island, and I had to help it several times. SCAR took 5 mins, and I took 3 mins(legit).

lilmatt56:

nexus is far better than scar imo

Yes, in your opinion, you see, if you stick to something good, people release good “tools” for it.

lilmatt56:

I Am Olan14 i think you mean KYAB by solarwind and benland which is private as far i know (you must apply for access by showing ur knowledge in programming)

SRL Members at the SRL forums get KYAB, however KYAB isn’t the only “supertool” for SCAR.
